pageContext.claim: “We are responding with great speed and professionalism.”
pageContext.analysis: The United States has lagged far behind other major countries in providing tests for possible cases. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention initially distributed flawed tests to state and local health departments. The lack of tests in the United States, compared with countries such as South Korea that have tested tens of thousands of people, has meant the possible spread of the virus in the country may not be fully known.
